tspan.tspan: The Toronto Healthy House required no public water, sewer, or gas utilities
and it provided most of its own electricity. The house, sponsored by the
Canadian Mortgage and Housing Corporation (CMHC), became widely
known in the region and at one point was featured on a Canadian stamp.
The potential was for homes that someday could be sited at lower cost in
areas where public utilities are not available and wells with septic systems
